13:18 <Enygma`> tmortagne: seems that when a wiki is deleted, the translations bundle cache is not properly cleared  
13:18 <Enygma`> so when a translations is rendered, it will hit document bundles from the deleted wiki and the loadDocument operation fails

16:24 <Enygma`> tmortagne: are you sure that cleaning the bundleCache is enough? Don`t you have to remove the bundles from the bundlesCache as well? If the translation is not found in the cache, it will ask the context for bundles and try to load it, then it will fail again.  
16:26 <tmortagne> Enygma`: not sure what you mean the bundle is removed from "bundlesCache" cache  
16:27 <tmortagne> that's the only thing #clear method does  
16:27 <tmortagne> the bundle ask the factory to remove itself from the cache  
16:28 <tmortagne> hmm but I forgot another thing  
16:29 <Enygma`> tmortagne: from what I understand, there are 2 things: bundlesContext (list of documents containing translations) and bundleCache (cached translations, a subset of bundlesContext used for performance reasons)  
16:30 <tmortagne> bundlesContext is regenerated at each request for except for the bundles at root level  
16:31 <tmortagne> but I need to make sure there is no component with the bundle anymore  
16:31 <tmortagne> I'm doing it now  
16:32 <tmortagne> ha no forget that  
16:32 <tmortagne> the component associated wiki are automatially cleaned  
16:32 <tmortagne> so all should be ok  
16:33 <tmortagne> Enygma`: bundleContext is only true in the current context and the current context wiki is not the deleted wiki usually I don't think I need to force cleaning it  
16:34 <tmortagne> you can look at DefaultTranslationBundleContext for how the context is created  
16:35 <tmortagne> it's just here to speed up a bit the thing in a context, to avoid asking the component manager each time you search for a translation  
16:39 <Enygma`> I just looked at DocumentTranslationBundleFactory and saw that it is a singleton that has only this.bundleContext.addBundle(bundle); calls, but no removals.  
16:39 <Enygma`> and thought that might be a problem, but you know the code better than I do

16:42 <Enygma`> so I can move on with the release
